You can have `onload` and `onerror` events bound to an image to check if the image exists. 

Sometimes the on error method doest work as expected when the 404 page is returned with a 200 status or browser sometimes doesn&#39;t fire on error you can check on load event the width n height should be positive 

So the image checker function returns a Promise either success/error you can have it work for you in your own way

```
function checkImage(src) {
  return new Promise(function(resolve, reject) {
    var image = new Image();
    image.onload = function() {
      if (!this.width &amp;&amp; !this.height) {
        this.onerror();
        return;
      }
      resolve(src);
    };
    image.onerror = reject;
    image.src = src;
  });
}
```

