If anybody that runs across this same thing, I finally figured out what the issue was. Whenever I was creating my `OfflineAudioContext`, I was initializing it wrongly. I was doing this

    let offline = new OfflineAudioContext(2, 44100 * buffer.duration, 44100);

when I should&#39;ve been doing

    let offline = new OfflineAudioContext(buffer.numberOfChannels, buffer.length, buffer.sampleRate);

After I made that change, the frequency data values between the offline context and the realtime one appeared much closer together.

